From 05b8abf0534e79699f42aab48996855a84a8bbda Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 17:10:51 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Redesign UI, simplify mascots, and add Firebase email auth
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

### Motivation
- Simplify visual identity to a minimal 2–3 color system, reduce emoji clutter and keep a single mascot representation to make the UI cleaner and more consistent.
- Remove mascot-selection flows and redundant UI choices to streamline onboarding/profile and the overall experience.
- Gate the app behind authentication and provide an email/password sign-in flow using Firebase to support persistent user sessions.
- Replace duplicated game shortcuts with three distinct game modes to improve gameplay variety and structure.

### Description
- Reworked theme: replaced the previous Duolingo-style palette with a compact `Primary`/`Accent`/neutral set in `ui/theme/Colors.kt` and updated `ui/theme/Theme.kt`, while keeping backward-compatible `Duo*` aliases for components.
- Simplified UI screens: removed mascot selection and many inline emojis, updated `ProfileScreen`, `HomeScreen`, and `ExerciseScreen` to a cleaner layout and added short mode hints in `ExerciseScreen`.
- Authentication: added `AuthRepository`, `AuthViewModel`, and `AuthScreen` and updated navigation (`NavGraph` and `Screen`) to show the auth screen when the user is not signed in; added Firebase Auth dependency to `app/build.gradle.kts`.
- Games and domain changes: introduced `GAME_RHYTHM`, `GAME_ECHO`, and `GAME_PUZZLE` modes in `domain/model/Exercise.kt`, updated default seeded exercises in `SpeechRepositoryImpl` and replaced repetitive quick-start entries with three unique game entries on `HomeScreen`.

### Testing
- Ran `./gradlew :app:assembleDebug` in this environment but the wrapper initially failed due to permission and then failed to download the Gradle distribution because of the environment proxy (error: `Unable to tunnel through proxy ... 403 Forbidden`), so a full build could not be completed here.
- No unit or instrumentation test suites were executed in this environment due to the build/download failure.
- Static checks (manual inspection and small local file edits) were applied and the project changes were committed for further CI/build verification in a network-enabled environment.
